129. caueant...credant‚ the formula of which this is a parody, was probably used in declarations of insolvency or minorship; caueant thus suggests the legal sense of taking precaution, security; credant suggests loans, but all that Pseudolus says is ‘take care not to believe me.'

130. ostium...erepuit, the regular indication that another character is going to enter the stage. Cf. Men. 348 concrepuit ostium, cf. sores concrepuerunt Mil. 409, Bacch. 610, aperitur ostium Capt. 108, aperitur foris Mil. 977.
